name: The Red Spider Nebula: surfing in Sagittarius - not for the faint-hearted!
description:
Huge waves are sculpted in this two-lobed nebula some 3000 light-years away in the constellation of Sagittarius.

Name:	NGC 6537, Red Spider Nebula
Type:	Milky Way : Nebula : Type : Planetary
Distance:	6000 light years
Constellation:	Sagittarius
Category:	Nebulae

3,629 editions for the known 3,629 planetary systems to date.

Credit: ESA/Hubble/NASA
